definitions: To fasten or secure with a key or keys.
To enter or operate on (data or a device) using a keyboard or keypad.
To adjust the pitch or tone of (a musical instrument or piece).
To scratch or damage (a car) with a key.
To provide with a key or legend, as for a map or diagram.
examples: He keyed the lock before leaving.
She keyed in the data quickly.
The piano was keyed to a lower pitch.
The map was keyed to the index.
